// ChaCha20 round-folding demo (Cryptol-only, non-trivial property):
// pins the *seed* semantics of the polymorphic-iterate lowering.
//
// Property: `iround 0 r == r` over the unmodified reference Cryptol
// `iround : [64] -> Round -> Round` from
// `deps/cryptol-specs/.../chacha20.cry`. The body
// `iround n r = (iterate once r) @ n` exercises the same
// polymorphic `Prelude.fix` shape as `core` (chacha20's private
// `iterate`), but with a non-reflexive equality — the discharge
// must actually reduce `iterate once r @ 0` to `r`, exercising
// `cryptolIterate_zero` rather than just `bvEq_refl`.
//
// Companion to `cryptol_chacha20_core_iterate` (which pins
// `core x == core x` via reflexivity). Together they cover both
// the "translation works at all" and the "translation has the
// right reduction behaviour" sides of the polymorphic-iterate
// lowering.

import "../../../../deps/cryptol-specs/Primitive/Symmetric/Cipher/Stream/chacha20.cry";

prove_print (offline_lean "test_cryptol_chacha20_iround_zero.eq")
  {{ \(r : [16][32]) -> iround 0 r == r }};
